        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Rutherfordton, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mill Spring, Green Creek, Lake Adger, and Harris.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
